1
00:00:01,596 --> 00:00:03,431
“Tell me about your family.”

2
00:00:03,431 --> 00:00:06,463
Which one? The loud one? The vanished one?

3
00:00:06,463 --> 00:00:11,887
The one that only shows up in dreams where the wallpaper sighs?

4
00:00:11,887 --> 00:00:16,596
They said it wasn’t therapy, just a ‘constellation session.’

5
00:00:16,596 --> 00:00:22,260
Put the mat down. Close your eyes. See what appears.

6
00:00:22,260 --> 00:00:27,256
Spoiler: it’s always Uncle Arthur trying to reheat beef.

7
00:00:27,606 --> 00:00:30,160
I lay on the rug with a headache halo,

8
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:33,112
Half a Greggs in my chest, heart soft and shallow.

9
00:00:33,112 --> 00:00:35,984
Dream slipped sideways, curtains blinked,

10
00:00:35,984 --> 00:00:38,137
Woke in a room that reeked of drink.

11
00:00:38,137 --> 00:00:41,649
There’s Dad—or was—grumbling in chainmail,

12
00:00:41,649 --> 00:00:44,042
Telling Alexa to “bring more ale.”

13
00:00:44,042 --> 00:00:46,755
Mum’s in armour, scrolling her phone,

14
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:49,308
Likes a grief post, sighs alone.

15
00:00:49,308 --> 00:00:52,180
There’s a knight in the oven, roasting pride,

16
00:00:52,180 --> 00:00:54,972
And Cousin Kay live-streams the ride.

17
00:00:54,972 --> 00:00:57,447
Merlin’s in the hallway burning sage,

18
00:00:57,447 --> 00:01:02,073
Talking about chakras and council tax rage.I ask, “What’s this?”

19
00:01:02,073 --> 00:01:06,352
They say: “Your legacy.”I say: “It smells like fear and celery.”

20
00:01:06,701 --> 00:01:08,058
Everyone in this room is me—

21
00:01:08,058 --> 00:01:11,968
Dressed in roles I didn’t choose to be.

22
00:01:11,968 --> 00:01:14,600
Echoes in my spine, names in my teeth,

23
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:17,552
Laugh like Dad, blink like Auntie Neith.

24
00:01:17,552 --> 00:01:22,021
This isn’t a dream, it’s a family tree—

25
00:01:22,021 --> 00:01:27,096
With roots in guilt and bad TV.

26
00:01:27,447 --> 00:01:30,239
They pass round trauma like mashed peas,

27
00:01:30,239 --> 00:01:33,111
Uncle G spends twenty minutes on 5G.

28
00:01:33,111 --> 00:01:35,903
Says Arthur’s sword was forged in cash,

29
00:01:35,903 --> 00:01:38,218
From someone’s divorce and a cymbal crash.

30
00:01:38,218 --> 00:01:41,569
Nain (my Nan) says nothing, just stirs her tea,

31
00:01:41,569 --> 00:01:44,201
I look in her cup and swear it sees me.

32
00:01:44,201 --> 00:01:46,754
There’s a baby crying in reverse,

33
00:01:46,754 --> 00:01:50,903
And someone’s arguing with a haunted purse.I try to leave,

34
00:01:50,903 --> 00:01:52,500
but the hallway folds—

35
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:58,004
Each door a rerun of stories told.Mam says, “Don’t you dare walk away,”

36
00:01:58,004 --> 00:02:00,927
But her voice is mine, on delay.

37
00:02:01,277 --> 00:02:03,989
You can’t outrun what sits in your chair.

38
00:02:03,989 --> 00:02:07,021
The stories get up when no one’s there.

39
00:02:07,021 --> 00:02:09,574
Say the name and the table shakes—

40
00:02:09,574 --> 00:02:12,655
You’re not the break, you’re what it makes.

41
00:02:13,004 --> 00:02:14,919
Everyone in this room is me—

42
00:02:14,919 --> 00:02:17,712
The hero, the villain, the cup of tea,

43
00:02:17,712 --> 00:02:20,105
The voice that says “don’t look at me.”

44
00:02:20,105 --> 00:02:22,818
I wasn’t born—I was cast in the scene,

45
00:02:22,818 --> 00:02:28,453
Of a dream that dreams of being seen.

46
00:02:28,802 --> 00:02:31,355
Dad stands up, points to the fridge,

47
00:02:31,355 --> 00:02:34,068
Says, “Son, that’s where we kept the bridge.”

48
00:02:34,068 --> 00:02:37,100
I laugh, then cry, then hide my face,

49
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:42,447
He hugs me hard in a stranger’s place.Guinevere’s sobbing into the toast,

50
00:02:42,447 --> 00:02:48,350
Says, “We all miss someone the most.”The wallpaper peels into faces known,

51
00:02:48,350 --> 00:02:54,335
Every pattern’s a voice I’ve outgrown.I say, “I don’t know who to be,”

52
00:02:54,335 --> 00:02:56,090
And the table whispers,

53
00:02:56,090 --> 00:03:00,479
“Just be three—The child, the now, the one who sees.”

54
00:03:00,479 --> 00:03:24,064
And I breathe for once without disease.

55
00:03:24,414 --> 00:03:27,447
Woke up on the rug, tea gone cold,

56
00:03:27,447 --> 00:03:30,080
Phone at 2%, stories old.

57
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:32,872
No thunder cracked, no choirs sang,

58
00:03:32,872 --> 00:03:35,585
Just a headache and a seagull’s clang.

59
00:03:35,585 --> 00:03:38,377
But I walked different through the street,

60
00:03:38,377 --> 00:03:41,250
Less armour. More two feet.

61
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:44,043
Didn’t call Mam, but I hummed her song,

62
00:03:44,043 --> 00:03:47,394
And smiled when I got the lyric wrong.

63
00:03:47,394 --> 00:03:51,861
Legacy’s not a crown, it’s a grin—

64
00:03:51,861 --> 00:03:59,091
That says “I’ve been through it, and I’m still in.”

65
00:03:59,441 --> 00:04:01,037
Everyone in this room is me—

66
00:04:01,037 --> 00:04:04,467
But I don’t have to play them endlessly.

67
00:04:04,467 --> 00:04:06,941
I set the table, cleared the plate,

68
00:04:06,941 --> 00:04:09,015
Waved at grief and said, “It’s late.”

69
00:04:09,015 --> 00:04:12,846
I’m not the knight, the king, the mess—

70
00:04:12,846 --> 00:04:17,552
I’m just the dreamer.

71
00:04:17,552 --> 00:04:18,959
And I said yes.

72
00:04:19,309 --> 00:04:21,940
So yeah. It’s weird.

73
00:04:21,940 --> 00:04:24,653
But I think I’m okay with weird.

74
00:04:24,653 --> 00:04:29,201
And if you ever wake up at a table that feels too crowded to breathe—

75
00:04:29,201 --> 00:04:31,036
Try laughing.

76
00:04:31,036 --> 00:04:33,829
That’s what got me out.
